17/06/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- Unknown gunmen shot and killed a policeman in Athens Wednesday (June 17th).
Two assailants on a motorbike opened fire on a police officer who was guarding the Patissia home of a witness in a terrorism trial.
The witness, Sofia Kyriakidou, testified against her former husband Angeletos Kanas, an alleged member of the terror group People's Revolutionary Struggle (ELA).
In other news, the Council on Foreign Affairs and Defence (KYSEA) adopted a proposal Tuesday to cut arms spending and reduce mandatory military service.
Arms spending will be cut by 15% this year, Defence Minister Vangelis Meimarakis said.
The measures are part of a government programme to cope with the economic crisis.
(SKAI, ANA-MPA, AFP, Reuters, AP, Naftemporiki, Vima, Ta Nea, Eleftheros Typos - 17/06/09, ANA-MPA, Reuters, AP - 16/06/09)
